title: Flooding near the Basin Reserve causing delays
text:
Flooding near the Basin Reserve causing delays Last updated 16:33, February 2 2017 NZTA 
Flooding is causing delays near the Basin Reserve. 
Surface flooding on State Highway 1 near the Basin Reserve is causing some delays to Wellington traffic. 
The flooding is situated near the intersection with Ellice St, as the capital experiences heavy rain on Thursday afternoon. 
The New Zealand Transport Agency are warning motorists to take extra care in the conditions. HEADS UP: Surface flooding #SH1 Basin Reserve near the intersection with Ellice Street is causing some delays. Please take extra care. ^EL pic.twitter.com/kTXdGcQGXx
